lation: 美品=NM (NOT Excellent or Beautiful). 並品=MP (NOT Good or Fair).\nDEFECT GUARD: If source states any defect, condition MUST NOT be Mint or NM.\nFor graded cards (PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC): use the numeric grade in title, not a verbal condition term.\nConservative grading: use the most conservative (lower) grade when source description is ambiguous.\n\nLANGUAGE VARIATIONS\n- 日本語/日本版/JP -> Japanese (always include in Title for eBay discoverability)\n- 英語版/English/EN -> English (if source confirms)\n- 繁体字中国語版/TW -> Chinese Traditional (if source confirms)\n- 簡体字中国語版/CN -> Chinese Simplified (if source confirms)\n- 韓国語版/KR -> Korean (if source confirms)\n- 独語版/German/DE -> German (if source confirms)\n- 仏語版/French/FR -> French (if source confirms)\n- スペイン語版/Spanish/ES -> Spanish (if source confirms)\n- イタリア語版/Italian/IT -> Italian (if source confirms)\n- ポルトガル語版/Portuguese/PT -> Portuguese (if source confirms)\n- ロシア語版/Russian/RU -> Russian (if source confirms)\n- Assume Japanese unless another language is explicitly stated.\n\nDEFECT MAPPING (JP -> EN)\nIf source explicitly states any defect, include under "Condition Notes:" in Description. Omitting known defects violates eBay policy.\n折れ / 折れ目=Crease\n軽微な折れ=Light crease\n白かけ / エッジ白かけ=Edge whitening / Edge wear\nコーナー白かけ=Corner wear / Corner whitening\n欠け / 角欠け=Corner chip / Missing corner\nセンタリング偏り=Off-center / Mis-center\nカット悪=Miscut / Bad cut\n傷 / 擦れ / スレ=Surface scratch\nニック=Nick\n反り / カール=Warping / Curling\nフォイル浮き / フォイルカール=Foil bubbling / Foil curling\nフォイル波打ち=Foil pringling\nフォイル剥がれ=Foil peeling\nテクスチャーフォイル剥がれ=Textured finish peeling\nラミネート分離=Delamination\nインク飛び / 印刷ミス=Print error / Misprint\n印刷ズレ=Print misalignment\nシミ / 汚れ=Stain / Smudge\nカビ=Mold / Mildew damage\n水ダメージ / 波打ち=Water damage\n日焼け / ヤケ=Yellowing / Sun damage\nテープ跡=Tape residue\n書き込み / マーク=Writing / Pen marks\n穴あき=Hole / Puncture\n裂け=Tear\n臭い=Odor / Smoke smell\n初期傷=Factory defect (NOT "early scratch")\nNOTE: Foil bubbles >1mm diameter = auto Damaged (TCGPlayer standard). Disclose bubble presence and size.\n\nACCESSORY DICTIONARY\nPOSITIVE (note if source confirms):\n- PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC鑑定済み -> PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC Graded (includes slab)\n- スリーブ入り -> With Sleeve\n- トップローダー入り -> With Top Loader\n- マグネットケース入り -> With Magnetic Case\nNEGATIVE (note only if source explicitly confirms absence):\n- スリーブなし -> No Sleeve\n- トップローダーなし -> No Top Loader\n- ケースなし -> No Grading Case\n\nEXCLUDE FROM OUTPUT (CRITICAL)\nThe source may contain seller descriptions NOT relevant to eBay listing:\n- Shipping information (発送, 送料, shipping, 宅急便)\n- Seller opinions (美品だと思います, 値下げ不可, 神経質な方)\n- Purchase instructions (即購入OK, コメントください)\n- Storage/handling (暗所にて保管, クリスタルパック)\n- PSA grade explanations (公式サイトより抜粋)\n- Warnings and disclaimers (注意事項, ご遠慮下さい)\n- Japanese hashtags that are NOT card/set names (#MTG, #PSA, #鑑定品, #GEMMINT, #日絵, #DAKEN)\n- Booster type indicators (these define the sealed product type, not card identity):\n  * セトブ = Set Booster / ドラブ = Draft Booster / コレブ = Collector Booster\n  (include in title ONLY when the sealed product itself is what is being sold)\n- Internal codes or long number sequences\n\nERA / EDITION MARKER\nDetect and include in Title/Description when source confirms:\n- Alpha / Beta / Unlimited (1993): black-border. Highest value.\n- Revised / 3rd Edition (1994): white-border. Common vintage.\n- Foreign Black Border (FBB): Japanese 4th Edition black-bordered = collector premium.\n- 1st Edition / First Edition: detect from 初版 / 1st Edition / First Edition in source.\n- Reserved List: WotC\'s 572 cards never to be reprinted. Include "Reserved List" in Description for these.\n- Promo: Prerelease / Judge Foil / Buy-a-Box / Arena / Launch Party — include promo type if stated.\nNICKNAME GUARD: Use Reserved List only when source states it or you can confirm the card is on the Reserved List. Never fabricate.\n\nTITLE (SEO Priority)\n- HARD LIMIT: 80 chars maximum. eBay rejects titles exceeding 80 chars.\n- GOAL: Maximize SEO