y when source explicitly states foil type\n- Borderless / Extended Art / Showcase / Retro Frame / Full Art — only when source states treatment\n- Serialized — only when source states serialized / numbered variant\n- Alpha / Beta / Unlimited / Revised / 4th Edition — only when source states edition\n- Foreign Black Border / FBB — only when source states this\n- Reserved List — only when source states reserved list or confirms a known reserved list card\n- 1st Edition / First Edition — only when source states 初版 / 1st Edition\n- Judge Foil / Prerelease / Buy-a-Box Promo — only when source states promo type\n- Commander / EDH — only when source states this format context\n- Mythic Rare / Rare / Uncommon / Common — only when rarity is stated in source\n\nDESCRIPTION (SEO Priority)\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain card name + set name.\n  Example: "Stoneforge Mystic Foil from Double Masters. Published by Wizards of the Coast."\n- Include searchable specs naturally: card name, foil/variant, set name, card number, language, grade, condition notes.\n- Publisher: "Published by Wizards of the Coast" — include once in Description.\n- Use keyword variations: "MTG" "Magic The Gathering" "Magic: The Gathering card"\n- For Reserved List cards: include "Reserved List" in Description.\n- NEVER include: shipping info, seller opinions, price negotiations.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: [Card Name] [Variant] [Set Name]\n- Examples:\n  Stoneforge Mystic Foil Double Masters\n  Sheoldred the Apocalypse Borderless Dominaria United\n  Ragavan Nimble Pilferer Showcase Modern Horizons 2\n  Black Lotus Alpha\n\nCATEGORY\n- Single card (graded or ungraded): 38292\n- Sealed booster pack: 183456\n- Sealed booster box / display box: 261044\n- Sealed commander deck / precon deck: 183457\n- Mixed lot / bulk card lot: 183455\n- Complete set: 183459\n\nCATEGORY RULE\n- Single card raw (any condition) -> 38292\n- Single card graded (PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC) -> 38292\n- Promo card -> 38292\n- Booster pack (sealed) -> 183456\n- Booster box / display (sealed) -> 261044\n- Commander precon / Sealed deck -> 183457\n- Mixed lot / bulk -> 183455\n- Complete set -> 183459\n- If unclear -> 38292\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title is 80 chars or under HARD LIMIT, uses only allowed symbols (& / : - . , # and \' for possessives).\n2. Description <= 480 chars, single paragraph, ASCII only, no CJK.\n3. No fabricated facts — every spec must derive from source.\n4. If graded card, grade appears at START of Title.\n5. "Published by Wizards of the Coast" appears in Description once.\n6. Card name appears in Title.\n7. If Foil or Variant detected in source, appears in Title.\n8. "Japanese" appears in Title unless source explicitly confirms another language.\n9. "MTG" appears in Title when space allows and source supports it.\n10. No shipping info or seller opinions in output.\n11. ProductName matches card name from Title.\n12. DEFECT GUARD: If defect noted in source, condition is NOT Mint or NM.\n13. No Bootleg/Proxy/Counterfeit/Replica/Fake anywhere in output.\n14. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };


